30/03/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The government has signed a $15m contract with Occidental Petroleum for oil and natural gas drilling in Shpiragu Mountain, 120km south of the capital. 
The US company been exploring the same area since 1991. 
An Occidental spokesman said the new drilling, due to start on 20 April, would finally determine if there is any oil or natural gas in the area.
In other news, Hungarian President Ferenc Madl kicks off a two-day visit to Albania on Wednesday. 
He will meet with Albanian counterpart Alfred Moisiu and other officials. 
(AP, Albanian government Web site - 29/03/05)
